inn1.comm: straightens immediately, and bounces from short of a length, close to off stump line, left alone
full, wide and moving in a shade, left alone
cramped for room as it holds its line after starting across, punched to extra cover
bowled much fuller now, he comes across, bat in front of pad and pushes to leg
nice leave, this wasn't far from off as it angled away, Tamim shouldered arms confidently
back of a length again, straightening, nudged to square leg
length ball chopped past backward point's dive to third man
holds the line, but starts on the pads and is tucked behind square
short of a length and he rides the bounce to steer it down to third man
pitched up on the pads and he brings bat around front pad to turn it through midwicket
pitched up around off now, he stretches forward to check the push to mid off
slanted wider outside off, fine bounce, left alone
climbing outside off, but widish and guided to thtrd man
angled across and ending on off, he is cramped and turns it softly to leg
overpitched, just outside off, and he reaches out to drive crisply past the non-striker
short of a length, he rides the bounce and punches on the up to cover

early strike for Chatara, Tamim has gone flashing outside off, this skidded across from short of a length, left Tamim further with the angle, he flashed anyway from the crease, and Taylor took the edge low in front of first slip
slants it across fuller across the left-hander, who leaves it alone
cracks this short of a length ball straight to cover
checks the punch and gets this widish one down to third man, Elton scrambles to stop the boundary after a fumble

top edge, and a sitter is put down by Chatara running in from fine leg, Ashraful went across to off and swung this short of a length ball in the air, Chatara ran in a long way, reached there in time, got both hands to it, and it popped out tamely
shout for lbw now as he misses the flick to a full delivery, there were two sounds, and it was also headed down leg
turned off the pad to square leg
pushes this length ball around off to covers
pitched up and right on off stump, he presses forward to block
a thick edge now to third man off a length ball, he is getting it to hurry after pitching
tight line going across close to off, he shoulders arms
too full but he cannot time the drive, to extra cover
diving stop at cover, he'd timed the drive alright this time, good backing up at short fine leg too
floated across, pitched up, and beats him on the drive this time
overpitched and he goes after it, can't place it wide of mid off
has a go at the drive again, this length ball moves away a shade to beat him
was preparing for the same shot but this was much closer to off, and he adjusted to drop it to the off side for a quick single
swivels and tries to hook, but this was a sharp and quick bouncer, and goes past his helmet
pitched up now on the stumps, softly turned to cover
back of a length but down leg and worked behind square
pushes forward for the drive, but the line is ending on off, and he does not have enough room to time it
good length and nippy around middle, squeezed towards covers, he is not getting the single
can't get hold of the drive again, pitched up and a hint of holding the line, thick inside edge into pad
good length on off now, he pushes with an open face to cover
dropped, Chatara again, but much tougher chance, Mominul is eager to drive everything pitched up, bat face closes and it pops up to the bowler's left, he gets a hand to it, just about
back of a length on the pads, played out square
loose from Ashraful, he flays at a shortish and wide one, clear sound, and keeper takes it, Ashraful stands there for a few moments before reluctantly walking off
Mushfiqur shows how its done, short and climbing outside off, Mushfiqur gets on top and glides it past backward point
he left this, but it jagged back in sharply from back of a length, and wasn't far from off, lots of bounce
length ball clipped off the pad to square leg
right forward and across to block a pitched up ball to covers
pitched up, he moves forward to push to extra cover
flashes late at this one leaving him widish with the angle, and it flies down to third man
holding the line after being angled in wide from the crease, Mushfiq moves across and gets behind the line to block
into the pads and turned wide of fine leg for a couple
good leave, this bounces from a good length close to off
on off stump from wide of the crease, he is behind the line to block
slightly wider of off stump, he takes a step out to let it go
full into the pads and he's whipped it over the man in the circle to the deep square leg boundary
calmly forward to block a pitched up ball on off
cramped for room, pushes in front of extra cover, and has to get back
on off stump again, fullish, he is across to defend to the bowler
swivels and pulls in the air, not in control, there is a man at deep square leg but he's managed to hit this in front of square
overpitched, eased to mid on
leading edge as he wants to turn this overpitched one to leg, it goes in the gap past extra cover for a couple
gets into a tangle, slips and falls flat into the crease as he works this off the pad to square leg
tries to go big, lofts it through vacant midwicket with a closed bat face
gets too far across and misses the nudge to square leg, takes the leg bye
guides this short of a length ball to point
belatedly tries to cut this one leaving him wide outside off and is beaten
starts just outside off on a fullish length, slight inward shape, left alone
too short and far too wide, sent on its way to the deep cover boundary
hello, where has this come from, Mushfiq's cranked up and slammed this high over midwicket from outside off, almost went all the way
slight outswing but starts widish, and is left alone
swinging away, but too far outside off, and slapped to the sweeper
holds the line on off and is driven back to the bowler
starts wide, and is cut away, but backward point saves it with a quick movement to this left
slanted from wide of the crease, full and down the pads
gets across and pushes a length ball to cover
fuller outside off, he gets forward to drive to cover
widish one pushed wide of cover for a quick single
pushed wide of mid on for another quick run
cramped outside off, runs this climbing length ball to point
moves in to the pad from a good length, he cannot work it away
overpitched ball slapped to the right of mid off for one
tries to reach out and drive a wide outswinger, misses
gets on top of the bounce to control the cut to deep point
back of a length, whipped in front of square leg
nudges it from off to midwicket for an easy single
holds the line a tad outside off, bouncing from back of a length, pushed to point
turned with the inward angle through square leg and Mushfiq races back for the second
tries to heave a back of a length ball over midwicket now, misses
short and wide, he chops the cut to point, Mominul has to rush back at the non-striker's as the throw comes in
overpitched on middle and leg, knocked down to long on
comes down the track and pulls it down to fine leg
swings into the pads, he misses the flick and it rolls square
opens the face and runs this length ball to point
that has gone through everything, Mominul charges out and misses a heave to an inswinger, which bounces over the leg stump, and beats the keeper's dive
gets hold of the pull this time but hits it straight to deep square leg
dabs this wide ball to backward point who dives to stop it
direct hit would have been tight, Mishfiq hesitated after pushing in front of cover and had to really hurry in the end, throw missed
umpire Cloete has given this, it was slanted fullish and sharply into the right-hander, who leaned too far across and missed the clip to leg, not sure this was hitting leg, lot of angle
chance of a run out, he would have been gone had the lob hit, Mominul dived for the crease after Shakib pushed softly in front of cover, fielder charged in and picked it up quickly but missed
driven through cover for a single
angled across wide and cut hard to the deep point boundary, past backward point's dive
thick outside edge now as he pushes uncertainly at a pitched up ball, in the air and down to third man
back of a length, tries to force it through midwicket but knocks it down the pitch
moves across, opens up and drops it softly down the pitch
bowler shouts for lbw, but that pitched clearly outside leg
another shout for lbw but this pitched up ball was swinging down leg as he missed the swing to midwicket
too full and too wide, he gets down on the knee and crunches it to the deep cover boundary
back of a length close to off, he guides this to backward point
drives this length ball to sweeper cover
comes down the track right away and turns it to deep square leg
into the pads, nudged to square leg
tossed up, on the pads, worked to deep square
full on middle and leg, and he gets down to thump a sweep to deep backward square leg
good length, but down the pads again, he sweeps it to deep backward square, who's moved finer
chance for a run out, there was hesitation, but short fine leg cannot pick up the ball, much to the captain and bowler's disappointment
this leaves the left-hander, he wafts at it far away from the body and is beaten
and again, this time he tries to punch from the crease and is beaten once more
dropped, this is seriously poor, how many catches can you drop in an innings, cut straight to backward point, and straight out of his hands
hit to sweeper cover for a single
allows it to hit the bat outside off and turns it to third man
back of a length ball punched to extra cover
nudged to fine leg off the pad
down the track and eases a flighted ball to long on
moves across and tucks behind square leg from middle
skips out and drives, midwicket parries it to the bowler with a dive
Mominul was walking out almost every ball to the spinner, this time he's done the same, stopped, missed the punch, Taylor's got the bails off, but Mominul's back foot is back on ground in time
a thick edge now to cover as Utseya straightens it on middle
cramped for room on off stump, runs a length ball to point
overpitchd, hit hard but straight to extra cover
full and wide, slapped away to sweeper cover
Zimbabwe take a catch! Jarvis holds on and ends Mominul's struggle, he slogged at a length ball and skied it over midwicket, Jarvis settled under it, and tumbled down as he took it head high
length ball turned off the pad to forward square leg
full outside off, knocked with the spin to long on
floated up high, full and down leg
makes some room and cuts hard, cover somehow manages to stop it
cuts against the slight turn and picks up one to the sweeper
swatted through midwicket, man runs in from the deep and keeps them to one
flat, short of a length, he runs it straight to short third man
fuller and some flight, pushed back
length ball around off, he checks the drive to extra cover
more width and he cuts, backward point goes flying to his left to stop it
pushes a pitched up ball on off to the bowler
calmly forward to block a full one around off
width again, and he cuts it hard, in the air, and over backward point
still more width, cut hard again, but to backward point
short of a length, turned off the pad to fine leg
almost hit it back to the bowler, pushed a full one in the air, bowler went down to his right, but it didn't carry
full and angled in, he pushes it back
overdoes the angle and overpitches it too, and is flicked over midwicket and into the boundary
pushes a length ball to cover from the crease
calm forward defence to the bowler
bounces from a length, he opens the face to guide it to third man
runs this pitched up ball to backward point
short and widish, cut to backward point
pitched up ball worked to mid on
goes back and guides a length ball to point
moves forward to keep out a length ball on middle stump
softly guides this length ball on off behind point for one
this nipped in from a length and hit him on the thigh pad, shout turned down, too high
hit high on the pad again as he goes back, third man slips and sends in a weak throw
checks a forcing drive down the pitch to a length ball
this time he drives, sends it racing through off, mid off slides across to stop it
wide, cut hard into the ground to one of the two backward points
stays in the crease and guides to third man from around off
short and wide, he cuts, past the two backward points, but sweeper cover is there too
squeezes a length ball to point, early call of no
opens the face and sends it from off wide of third man
pitched up, pushed back to the bowler
turned off the pad behind square leg
chops a cut to backward point
he cuts in front of square now, to sweeper cover
wide delivery cut straight to backward point number one
angled in from wide of the crease, thick inside edge onto pad as he pushes with an angled bat
short into the body, he swivelsand swings it down to fine leg
moves in from outside leg stump, turned square for one
short, pulled hard to deep square leg
back of a length ball turned to third man
drops it in front of point and takes the single, throw misses at the striker's end
jags back in from a good length, he is surprised and stabs it away to off
pitched up on off, he is forward to defend
back of a length, into the pads, turned to deep square
turned with the spin from the crease to square leg
goes back to pull through midwicket, it is stopped just inside the boundary by long on after deep midwicket misses with the slide

Shakib is furious at this decision, he's hit his bat hard into the crease before turning and walking off, caught in front of middle with a straightening, flighted good length offbreak, was there an inside edge? can't pick one on replays, he'd closed the face as he tried to turn it to leg, almost hit Taylor as he swished in anger, then apologised as he went back
forward to block a tossed up ball
turned to midwicket
goes across to block to the off side
cut to the sweeper for a single
pushed off the front foot to cover
reaches out at a widish, gentle, full one, and runs it to point
softly pushed to extra cover
overpitched, hit down to long on
back of a length ball nudged in front of midwicket for one
full delivery turned to square leg
tossed up straighter one, he is beaten on the cut
and this is fired full, quick and wide down leg
chops the cut to cover
works it behind square leg and trots out, is slow to turn back, there is a direct hit, but he's in, they run off the ricochet
turns it in the air to midwicket
flat and quick, worked to midwicket, bowler runs in front of the fielder and stop it
short and nipping in, pulled in the air but short of deep midwicket
short and wide, dabbed to deep point
cracks a widish length ball to deep point
goes across and defends a length ball down the pitch
beaten as he goes pushing at a quite wide one
overpitched, pushed back to the bowler
too full, patted to extra cover
flat and quick, pushed to point
punched down the pitch for the bowler to make a diving stop
overpitched and angled in, turned to deep midwicket
flat delivery punched to sweeper cover
square driven to sweeper cover
appears to go for a big drive and checks it in the end as the length ball does not quite come on
cramped for room with one angled in to off
runs it behind point for a single
back of a length, steered to third man
turned off the pad in front of midwicket for a quick single
angled down the leg side, umpire calls an over, and Mahmudullah can't believe a wide wasn't called
tossed up full and carted high over the long off boundary, mid off is up
flatter and into the pads, turned to deep square
turned from outside off to square leg
comes down the track, he shortens it, Nasir stops and runs it to short third man
reverse paddles from outside off and picks up two to fine third man
tossed up ball knocked down to long on
short of a length, pushed to cover off the back foot
goes for the pull, hits it loopily over midwicket
steers this from close to off, to third man
short and wide, flashed in the air down to third man
worked in front of midwicket for a single
short of a length, swatted to deep square leg
short outside off, he swivels and pulls hard to deep midwicket
another wicket for Chatara, Nasir tried to dab this short, skiddy delivery past the keeper, guided it straight into Taylor's gloves, he is quite disappointed as he walks off
pushed down the leg side on a good length
defends this length ball on off to point
moves across and knocks a length ball back to the bowler
full into the pads, clipped in the air, couple of bounces to deep square
that shortish one stayed a shade low, dragged from outside off to deep midwicket
on the pads with fine leg up, he turns it past the man in the circle
full one turned to midwicket
that nipped in from back of a length and went past the inside edge
moves across and turns it from middle and leg to deep midwicket
pushes to cover and wants the single, is sent back
guides this from close to off to backward point
quick and full, pushed to long off
flat and short of a length, worked to long on
driven through extra cover, long off is wide
floated full and down the leg side, short fine chases, Ziaur wants a second, but gets back in time
turned to midwicket
low full toss eased to long on
short and wide, cut to sweeper cover
length ball pushed down the pitch towards the leg side
goes for the yorker from wide of the crease, it's turned to midwicket
goes for a drive to a wide one and is beaten as it moves away after pitching
tries the drive again, hits it down the track off the inner part of the bat
pitched up outside off, pushed to the bowler

soft dismissal, leading edge sails to point as Ziaur tries to work a back of a length ball from outside off to leg, Chatara celebrates, but hang on, he's overstepped, he's got nothing behind the line when he lands
tries to slog this wide and slower one beyond deep midwicket but misses
pushes a length ball to point for a single
dipping full delivery, turned to deep square leg
beaten by a slower one, goes pushing at it wide outside off
pitched up delivery hit hard to mid off past the bowler's dive
another slower one, pitched up, he pats it back
coming in from outside off, pushed softly towards point
back of a length, turns it from outside off to deep midwicket
slow and full, way down the leg side
works a short of a length ball to deep midwicket, who keeps them to one
charges out and drives it along the ground to sweeper cover
long appeal upheld, he's tried to pull this short one going down the leg side, and gloved it on its way low to the keeper
short again, he's surprised and fended it into the off side
tries to pull, can't get hold of it, ball rolls onto the pitch, non-striker charges up, but gets back even as bowler gets to the ball
shorter, this time he is on top of the bounce to pull, to deep midwicket
short outside off and angling away, he cannot connect as he tries to dab it to third man
turned to fine leg off the pad
slower length ball turned in front of square leg, bowler rushes after it, and Mahmudullah sends back Razzak
Razzak's got one away, overpitched around off and he's slammed it over long off boundary
makes room outside leg, bowler follows him, he nudges it behind square leg
angled in on a length, he's softly turned this to leg for one
goes across, brings bat around pad and flicks it past short fine's dive
loopy full slower one, he backs away and adjusts to glide it to the sweeper
overpitched, he's cleared front leg and swung it dead straight down the ground
he's liking this angle from round the wicket, has cranked up and slogged this from outside off over deep midwicket
on top of the bounce to cut to deep point
jumps to pull a short ball to deep midwicket
straight to short fine leg, bonus wicket, Mahmudullah skips out, and turns it right to the fielder off his pads
pitched up to off, defended to point, Razzak sends him back
angled into the pads, worked in the air past midwicket
length ball slanted across, slapped past extra cover for a couple
goes for the yorker, it's turned to midwicket off the pads, non-striker has to get back quickly
cuts this from close to off stump, third man does well to run across and slide
little gem this from Razzak, he walks across and manages to swing a short ball wide of short fine leg
dropped, Razzak top-edges a slog, Jarvis runs back on off, it comes over his shoulder, he gets both hands to it but it pops out, there was a run out chance, at either end, but they survive
swings and misses at a good length ball around off
overpitched on leg, swung off a thick inside edge to short fine

what a fortuitous run out in the end, Razzak squeezed a push to short third man, before he knew it, Shafiul had charged across to his end, the throw came in on the bounce to the bowler, and ricocheted into the stumps off Shingi's thigh as he missed the take
Razzak's murdered this length delivery way, way over deep midwicket, it's cleared the trees surrounding the boundary comfortably, that ball is not coming back
length again, on the pads now, and he's lifted it between deep midwicket and long on, what an assault
this could have gone as well, high and wide full toss, off to third man with a thick edge
pushes a length delivery solidly to extra cover
loud appeal for lbw, turned down, Razzak missed the slog as he went across, but that has pitched outside leg
Razzak's sent another one over the boundary, long on this time, moves a long way outside leg, and blasts a full one out of sight
stands outside leg and misses a back of a length ball outside off
incredible, now he's pulled him over deep midwicket for a flat six, off the front foot
he gets to fifty in 21 balls, slapping a short and wide delivery over cover, the dressing room applauds, he's absolutely stunned Zimbabwe
full on the pads, away to short fine leg

inn2.comm: back of a length and knocked down to gully
full and wide, and swinging away now
several feet outside off, another leave
outswinger, full and quite wide
much closer to off, he is forward to push to point
outswinger again, widish and he lets it go
charges out first ball and lifts a length outswinger to third man off a thick outside edge
that could have been close, it was pitched up straight on off, he scrambled across to defend
wayward delivery miles down leg, keeper dives to get a glove to it
good length ball pushed to forward square leg
overpitched on the pads and he's lifted it over midwicket for three
walks down, stops and tries to pull over square leg, is hit on the body
forward to a length delivery and puts it away through cover
that swung in sharply as it approached the keeper after batsman left it alone
short of a length, off the pads to fine leg
straightening from a length, but starting too far outside off and he punches it to the deep point rope
overpitched now, wide again, swinging away and he crashes it past cover's drive
shoulders arms to a straightish pitched up ball
lovely, holds the line after being angled in and beats the edge by a long margin
good length outswinger going away from close to off, left alone
charges out and heaves, picks up a single off a thick inside edge to short fine leg
swings away but several miles outside off
overpitches now on middle and leg, it is straightening, but Sibanda's flicked this powerfully through midwicket
defends a back of a length ball moving away a shade on off
short and wide, he crashes a cut to point
nudges to leg, forward square leg cannot get to it in time and a single is on
that could have been close, he was late in getting forward to this pitched up ball, saved by a thick inside edge to square leg
he's gone through him, full and straight on off from Shafiul, Masakadza's played all around it, trying to hit it to leg and lost his off stump
lunges forward to defend this length ball and is beaten as it just about holds its line
full and angled in, leading edge as he wants to go leg side but gets it striaght past the bowler
widish, and punched with an open face through point off the back foot
pushes forward and drives it into the ground, over short extra cover
that's come back in a long way to him high on the pad, too much height and angle
charges out again and slaps a length ball to short extra cove
widish back of a length ball driven to the left of cover for one
slashes this short and widish one on the bounce to third man
short around off, and Sibanda gets the pull going off the front foot, it rolls into the deep midwicket rope
widish length ball square driven to point
goes across and pushes a short of a length ball, in the air for a while, to mid on
comes forward and across, and brings bat in front to drive elegantly through midwicket
pushes a length ball outside off to short extra cover, held its line that one
that is a loud shout, but turned down, it was angled in, hit him on the knee roll in front of middle and leg, that is not a bad shout at all
gets behind the line to defend a length ball on off
drilled to the deep cover boundary
punched to extra cover from the crease
flighted, and that's been lofted down the ground for four, was not that far from mid on
hit on the pad down the leg side
cut to cover from close to off
fullish, driven down to long off
stretches forward to defend down the track
defends a good length ball on off
short of a length and too wide, he's cut it in front of square and got enough on it to beat the chasing fielder
short and wide once more., Sibanda waits and goes behind point now, and harder on the cut, beating sweeper cover comfortably
Sibanda playing a shot a ball, charges out and heaves it over midwicket, it's pulled back inches inside as Mahmudullah goes flying over the boundary with the effort
width, but he's punched it to point, and it was in the air for a while too
this is an atrocious over, this would have been wide had he let it go, but he 's reached out and hammered the cut past point
punched through the off side for a single off the back foot
beaten in the flight, almost falls over as he reaches forward, thick inside edge to square leg
lunges forward to defend down the pitch
fired in quick and flat, he gets bat down in time
draws him forward, gets some turn, he defends
better start from Ziaur, pitched up closer to off, thick inside edge as he tries to drive
pushes softly to the off side and wants the single, is sent back in time
he's walked out, Ziaur's angle it to the pad, and Sibanda's sent it to deep square leg with a clip
walks across and shoulders arms to a length ball
walks out and works it wide of deep midwicket for a couple
shot of the day, as far as elegance goes, he's leaned into the overpitched delivery and caressed it right between extra cover and mid off
comes forward to defend a tossed up full ball
shout for lbw, but that was missing leg with the angle
opens the face as he comes forward to push to point
drives a quicker one to wide long off
another loud shout turned down, there is no reason why it should have been, that is hitting leg stump, no problems with the height, he walked too far across and missed the work to leg
driven to long off
nudged to backward square leg off the pad
skips out and awkwardly defends down the pitch
angled in on a length, he cannot work it away
shortish, and he rocks back to pull to deep square leg
shortish again, driven wide of sweeper cover
tossed up ball guided to backward point
length delivery squeezed out to point
flighted quick, defended off the front foot
touch flatter, he punches to extra cover
punched to mid on for a quick single
some turn outside off, eased to the sweeper
knocks it square on the off side
guides this to short third man off the front foot
tossed up full, pushed to the bowler
punched off the back foot to long off
skips out and pushes to extra cover
leaves the crease again and drives to sweeper cover
wide and flat, cut wide of the sweeper
fired full down the leg side and it's tickled fine past the keeper
comes forward to push to extra cover
not that short, but Sibanda's opened up quickly to pull this wide of deep forward square leg
fired flat into the pads and rolls away
punched to midwicket off the pad
shortish again and he drags it to deep square
shout for lbw, but Shakib knows that was a thick inside edge onto pad, and has hands on his face in disappointment
cut to the sweeper for one
tossed up slow, and driven to long off
he's been given after a long appeal, another start not quite converted by Sibanda, goes down on the knee for the sweep, misses, this pitches around middle and hits in front of middle and leg
defended off the front foot
and another appeal for lbw, turned down, hit him in front of middle and off, but there were two sounds
soft dismissal, Raza's been moving across regularly to work to leg, and this time he's chipped it tamely to midwicket
pushes it softly in front of cover and takes a quick single
stretches forward to defend a length ball on off
forward again to block another one on off
reaches forward to drive to short extra cover
drives one angled across to sweeper cover
pushes a full one to long off
whipped off the pads to deep square leg
pushes a quick and full one to long off
full on the pads, worked to deep square
angled in, hits the pads and rolls square
middle and leg, full, turned to midwicket
punches a short of a length ball to short extra
angled in full, off the pad to square leg
leg side again, turned behind square
pushes a length ball on off to cover
pacy length ball beating the defensive push around off stump
pushes off the front foot, thick inside edge square on leg and they take the single
pushes in front of cover for a single, the throw is weak, and Taylor is home comfortably
pushes to the bowler off the front foot
full, pushed to the off side
gets the single to long off finally
wide length ball cut to the sweeper cover
full and slanted across, driven to point
defended off the front foot
drives, and wide of the sweeper, but not far enough from him, he keeps them to two
width given, but he finds point with the cut
underedges  a cut to the keeper
punches a flat one to extra cover
blocked off the front foot
skips out and defends back to the bowler
lovely, it's angled in full and he's lofted it confidently over extra cover with a step outside
quick and angled in full, defended
low full toss eased down to long on
tight, very tight, Taylor wanted the single after guiding it behind point, he was down a long way before turning, throw missed anyway
down to third man for a single
angled in, pushed to point
swishes at a cut to a widish one and is beaten
dug in short, he withdraws out of the pull and lets it sail past
tries a reverse, hits it to short third man
walks outside off to nudge to midwicket for one
driven to a diving short extra cover
knocked back to the bowler off the front foot
punched down to long off for a single
nudged to midwicket from outside off
pushes in front of cover, Taylor wants the single, not getting it
angled in to middle from round the stumps and turned to deep square
length ball punched to sweeper cover
